name.text: Köpa Hus Utomlands - Stockholm
name.html: Köpa Hus Utomlands - Stockholm

description.text:
Allt tyder nu på att det är köpläge. Räntan är låg och fastighetspriserna har sjunkit på 
många håll i världen.
Sedan 15 år tillbaka arrangerar Fair Media International AB fastighetsmässor i Norden 
för köp av bostäder utomlands.
Nästa mässa i Stockholm blir den 12-13 oktober 2019. 
Mässan äger rum på Globen Annexet.
Mässorna är en marknadsplats för utställare från hela världen som 
vill marknadsföra sina bostäder till kvalificerade köpare. 
Våra utställare på mässorna kommer från cirka 15 olika länder
och består av agenter, fastighetsmäklare och byggmästare  
samt andra företag som har med ämnesområdet att göra.
Vi arrangerar olika seminarier som är helt gratis för allmänheten. 
I mässbroschyren ges också information om seminarierna som 
kommer att presenteras och vilka som är seminarieföreläsare. 
Normalt hålls seminarier om olika populära länder i hela världen 
samt speciella seminarier om skattekonsekvenser vid köp av 
bostad utomlands, pensionering utomlands och 
hur man lyckas med en utlandsflytt.

description.text: Crammerock is een tweedaags, complexloos muziekfestival tijdens het eerste weekend van september in Stekene, tussen Antwerpen en Gent. Jaarlijks passeren meer dan vijftig bands op de drie podia, die garant staan voor non-stop muziek uit alle genres. Dankzij een uitmuntend collectief aan vrijwilligers weet het festival zich te onderscheiden met lage ticketprijzen en een opvallend ongedwongen sfeer. De vorige editie klokte het festival af op meer dan 35.000 bezoekers. Op de line-up dit jaar meer dan 50 nationale en internationale acts waaronder The Vaccines, Black Box Revelation, Bazart, Goose, Lil Kleine, Circa Waves, Enter Shikari & Craig David. Many more to be announced. Bekijk de volledige line-up op www.crammerock.be .

description.text:
Hollywood meets Ruhrpott: Seid dabei, wenn die GERMAN COMIC CON Dortmund am 7. - 8. Dezember 2019 zum 5. Mal traditionell die Wintertore öffnet!
Vor Ort erwartet die Besucher ein prall gefülltes Programm. Egal ob Nerds, Geeks, Hipster oder Familien – hier ist für alle etwas dabei: Action und Unterhaltung mit den Stars auf der großen Bühne, Panels, Photo Shoots und Autogrammstunden. Ein großer Cosplay-Contest, Comics, Mangas, Animes, Zeichner, Photopoints, Workshops, Games, Merchandise soweit das Auge reicht und vieles mehr. Ein Wochenende voller Entertainment für die ganze Familie!

ÖFFNUNGSZEITEN
Samstag, 07.12.2019; 9:00/10:00 - 18:00 Uhr 
Sonntag, 08.12.2019; 9:00/10:00 - 17:00 Uhr 
  
Besitzer von VIP-Tickets und Early Bird Tickets haben bereits ab 9 Uhr Zutritt zum Event.Alle Besucher mit einer normalen Tageskarte oder einem Wochenendticket haben ab 10 Uhr Zutritt. 
Kinder 0-5: Freier Eintritt in Begleitung eines Erziehungsberechtigten.Kinder 6-12: Vergünstigte Kindertickets in Begleitung eines Erziehungsberechtigten.
Altersnachweise müssen bei Bedarf vorgezeigt werden. 
Hat der Erziehungsberechtigte ein EARLY BIRD Ticket, kann das Kind auch mit einem normalen Ticket die Veranstaltung früher betreten.
 
Wichtige Info
WOCHENENDTICKET UND VIP TICKET BESITZER bekommen vor Ort beim Einlass ein Bändchen um ihr Handgelenk. Dieses Bändchen ist das komplette Wochenende am Handgelenk zu tragen. Sollte das Bändchen am Samstagabend abgemacht und Sonntag ohne das Bändchen am Handgelenk erschienen werden, wird der Zutritt auf die Convention verweigert.
Die VIP Ticket Inhaber erhalten ihre Gutscheine und Goodies direkt am Einlass beim Betreten der Halle.

Quick & Dirty: Die meistgestellten Fragen auf einen Blick

 Kann ich mein Kind mit zum Event bringen?
Es gibt keine Altersbeschränkung für das Event. Kinder  und Jugendliche  im  Alter von  1  bis  14  Jahren haben  nur Zutritt  in Begleitung  einer personensorgeberechtigten  oder  einer erziehungsbeauftragten  Person. Personensorgeberechtigte Person  ist,  wem allein  oder  gemeinsam mit  einer  anderen Person  nach  den Vorschriften  des Bürgerlichen   Gesetzbuchs   die  Personensorge   zusteht   (§   1   Abs.  1   Nr.   3  JuSchG).   Eine erziehungsbeauftragte Person ist jede Person über 18 Jahren, soweit sie auf Dauer oder zeitweise aufgrund  einer   Vereinbarung   mit  der   personensorgeberechtigten   Person  Erziehungsaufgaben wahrnimmt oder soweit sie ein Kind oder eine jugendliche Person im Rahmen der Ausbildung oder der Jugendhilfe betreut (§ 1 Abs. 1 Nr. 4 JuSchG).
 
Sind Rückerstattungen möglich?
Gekaufte Tickets sind von der Rückgabe und Stornierung generell augeschlossen. Dies gilt grundsätzlich für alle Eintritts-, VIP-, Photo Shoot-, Autogramm-, Diamond Pass-, Meet & Greet Tickets. Sollte ein Gast absagen und nicht zur Veranstaltung erscheinen, besteht kein Anspruch auf die Erstattung der Eintritts- und VIP Tickets. Gekaufte Photo Shoot / Autogramm / Meet & Greet / Diamond Pass Tickets für den entsprechenden Gast werden in einem Gast-Absage-Fall automatisch auf das Konto erstattet, mit dem sie bezahlt wurden.
  
Muss ich das ausgedruckte Ticket mitbringen?
Ja, die Tickets sind in ausgedruckter Form mitzubringen. Das Ticket muss zum Einlass vorliegen und in einem scannbaren Zustand sein.Achtung: Der QR Code ist nur einmal scanbar. Nach dem Scannen ist das Ticket entwertet.
  
Ist es ein Problem, wenn der Name auf dem Ticket nicht mit dem Namen des Teilnehmers übereinstimmt?
Das ist kein Problem. Die Tickets sind nicht personalisiert. Der Name auf dem Ticket muss nicht zwangsläufig mit dem Namen des Teilnehmers übereinstimmen.
 
Benötigen Schwerbehinderte und deren Begleitperson ein Eintrittsticket?
Begleitpersonen eines Schwerbehinderten mit der Kennzeichnung "B" im Ausweis haben kostenlosen Eintritt, so sie als Hilfsperson für den Schwerbehinderten notwendig sind. Schwerbehinderte benötigen ein normales Eintrittsticket für das Event.

description.text:
doTERRA 2019 Global Convention
Order your Healing Hands Foundation Service Project tickets & Yoga with Elena Brower tickets are now on sale! Get yours today! Select the green "Tickets" button and scroll down. 
We've reached max capacity for general sessions, and full conference passes are officially sold out! Email convention@doterra.com to be added to the wait-list should a ticket become available. We are beyond excited to gather together as a doTERRA community this fall!
Join us at doTERRA's Annual Global Convention September 10th-13th, 2019 in Salt Lake City to learn and celebrate! Find out more about essential oils, be inspired, and discover how you can impact lives for good. We look forward to seeing you there!
New this year, registration will open early on Monday evening. The Recognition Gala will take place on Tuesday night, and the General Sessions will take place on Wednesday, Thursday, and Friday. Empowered Success will wrap up the week on Saturday morning. 

Ticket Transfers and Cancellations 


Ticket transfer: Free (April 1–August 20, 2019). Ticket can only be transferred once. Payment is arranged by ticket holders and not facilitated by doTERRA. 


Ticket cancellation: Free (April 1–August 20, 2019)



Ticket Transfer Policy:
We can only transfer your entire order, meaning your general session ticket and all activity tickets (such as Gala, Empowered Success, Campus Tours, and Yoga) will be transferred. 
To transfer individual activity tickets - UPDATE AS OF 8/13/2019 - In an effort to make your convention experience more efficient and continue doTERRA’s commitment to eco-friendliness, printed activity tickets will no longer be available for trade or transfer on-site. All tickets will be contained within a QR code located on your badge. For questions, please email convention@doterra.com no later than August 20, 2019.
Fee: Free April 1–August 20. A ticket can only be transferred once.
To process your ticket transfer, email convention@doterra.com or call Member Services with your request.
Payment for transfers is arranged by you entirely. We do not transfer the payment to the new ticket holder.

Cancellation Policy:
Fee: Free April 1–August 20. 
To process your cancellation, email convention@doterra.com or call Member Services with your cancellation request. 

Track Changes Policy:
Track changes are possible based on availability. We cannot make any exceptions if tracks are already full. Email convention@doterra.com or call Member Services for track change requests.

Registration Questions 
For convention related requests, email convention@doterra.com or contact Member Services via the Live Chat link on http://doterra.com or at 1-800-411-8151. 

Please Note: 
*You must purchase a Full Conference Pass, in order to purchase any Activity Tickets. If you do not purchase a Full Conference Pass, your Activity Ticket(s) will be cancelled and refunded.
*Children under the age of 14 will not be permitted unless express written consent is given by dōTERRA. If consent is given, a separate ticket for the child will still need to be purchased. No children will be allowed at the Gala.


Convention Mondiale doTERRA 2019

Rejoignez-nous à la convention mondiale annuelle de doTERRA du 10 au 13 septembre 2019 à Salt Lake City pour apprendre et célébrer avec nous! Venez en apprendre davantage sur les huiles essentielles, être inspiré et découvrir comment vous pouvez changer les choses et avoir un impact positif sur la vie de votre entourage. Nous avons hâte de vous y voir!

Tout nouveau cette année! Le gala de reconnaissance aura lieu mardi soir et les sessions générales auront lieu mercredi, jeudi et vendredi. Cependant, nous ouvrirons les inscriptions tôt lundi soir et une présentation "clé du succès" clôturera la semaine le samedi matin.

Transferts de billets et annulation


Transfert de billet : Gratuit (1er Avril – 20 Août 2019). Un billet ne peut être transféré qu'une seule fois. Le paiement des transferts est entièrement arrangé par vous. Nous ne transférons pas le paiement au nouveau détenteur de billet.


Annulation du billet: Gratuit (1er Avril – 20 Août 2019).


Politique de transfert de billets
Gratuit: du 1er avril au 20 août. Un billet ne peut être transféré qu'une seule fois.
Pour traiter votre transfert de billet, envoyez un e-mail à convention@doterra.com ou appelez le service clientèle avec votre demande de transfert.
Le paiement des transferts est entièrement arrangé par les personnes impliquées. Nous ne transférons pas le paiement au nouveau détenteur de billet.
Nous ne pouvons transférer que la totalité de votre commande, ce qui signifie que votre ticket de session générale et tous les tickets d'activité supplémentaires achetés seront transférés. Cela comprend le gala, la formation "clé du succès", les visites de campus et le yoga.
Pour transférer des billets d'activité individuels, il vous suffit de les remettre à qui vous souhaitez les transférer sur place lors de l'événement. Le paiement est arrangé par les personnes impliquées.
Politique d'annulation
Gratuit: 1er avril au 20 août.
Envoyez un e-mail à convention@doterra.com ou appelez le service clientèle avec votre demande d'annulation.
Politique de changement de piste (A/B)
Le changement de pistes est possible en fonction de leurs disponibilités. Nous ne pouvons pas faire d'exception si les pistes sont déjà pleines. Envoyez un e-mail à convention@doterra.com ou appelez le service clientèle pour les demandes de changement de piste. Les changements de piste peuvent être faits jusqu'au 20 Août.
Questions sur l'inscription
Pour les questions concerncant la convention, veuillez envoyer un courriel à convention@doterra.com ou contactez le service clientèle au1-800-411-8151. 
Veuillez noter: 
*Vous devez acheter un pass complet pour la convention pour pouvoir acheter des billets d'activité (Gala, yoga, formation "clé du succès", etc.). Si vous n'achetez pas de pass de convention complet, vos tickets d'activité seront annulés / remboursés.
*Les enfants de moins de 14 ans ne seront pas autorisés à moins d'un consentement écrit exprès de doTERRA. Si le consentement est donné, un billet séparé pour l'enfant devra quand même être acheté. Aucun enfant ne sera admis au gala.

name.text: Inscripción sorteo de entradas TEDxRíodelaPlata2019: Los próximos 10 años
name.html: Inscripción sorteo de entradas TEDxRíodelaPlata2019: Los próximos 10 años

description.text:
Se nos ocurrió que la mejor manera de celebrar los 10 años de TEDxRíodelaPlata era invitar a nuestra comunidad a hacer un viaje. 
Un viaje a "los próximos 10 años". No porque nos guste hacer predicciones (somos bastante malos en eso) sino porque entender lo que está pasando ahora puede darnos herramientas para estar mejor parados para lo que se viene. Celebraremos las ideas, nuestra comunidad y los vínculos que nos hacen crecer a todos.
Si querés ser parte de este viaje tenés 2 opciones: anotarte, hasta el viernes 20 de septiembre, al sorteo de entradas gratuitas presionando el botón verde que dice "Inscribirse" u obtener tu entrada ahora mismo haciéndote Tlover (donante individual) ingresando acá. ¡Reservamos un número limitado de lugares para los Tlovers así que no te dejes estar!
Si optás por participar en el sorteo de entradas gratuitas, te avisaremos por email después del 20/9 si tuviste suerte o no.
Si optás por hacerte Tlover, aparte de nuestro agradecimiento eterno, nos contactaremos con vos para hacerte llegar tu entrada y contarte más sobre los beneficios y actividades exclusivas que podrás disfrutar antes, durante y después del evento.
Te contamos que la última vez que hicimos un evento para 10.000 personas se anotaron 60.000 al sorteo de entradas. Entonces decidimos esta vez ¡hacer dos funciones, con el mismo contenido y 10.000 personas en cada una! Así más gente puede vivir la experiencia TEDxRíodelaPlata en persona. Las funciones son:


Función 1: miércoles 23 de octubre de 13:00 a 21:00


Función 2: jueves 24 de octubre de 08:30 a 17:00


Te vamos a preguntar tus preferencia de fecha en el formulario de inscripción al sorteo. Si te hacés Tlover te vamos a contactar directamente para que nos digas a qué función querés venir.
Conocé más sobre TEDxRíodelaPlata acá.

description.text:
One Fine Baby is the must-attend, experiential fair for new parents - and it’s FREE! 
SATURDAY 14th September 2019 --> 10am -3pm
SUNDAY 15th September 2019 --> 10am -3pm
Known as one of the most stylish baby fairs in Australia, One Fine Baby features a mix of vendors you simply can’t find anywhere else. This FREE two-day event at the Royal Exhibition Building brings together 100+ must-have brands & services. These premium, creative brands include maternity wear, skin care, baby goods, fashion, books, furniture & interiors, photographers and lifestyle services. Nowhere else can you find such a unique mix under one roof! 
Enjoy the buzzing atmosphere, with show specials, competitions and giveaways. Bring the whole family - there will be craft activities, play areas and entertainment, delicious food and coffee. Endota Spa together with Incy Interiors will be providing an area for guests to feed their babies in a relaxing and calm environment within the event.One Fine Baby is an essential for expecting parents, with experts on hand to educate you on First Aid, Nutrition (for Mum and Baby), Breastfeeding and Pre and Postnatal Care.
The fair features products and ideas for expecting parents and babies, as well as children aged 1-5.Don’t miss Australia’s most stylish show for bump, baby...and beyond!
TINY HEARTS FIRST AID CHOKING WORKSHOPS  - 11am // 12pm// 2pm Both Saturday and Sunday
FAQs
What are my transport/parking options for getting to and from the event?
Public Transport
Plan your trip using PTV's Journey Planner. Transport options include:

Tram route 86 or tram route 96 to corner of Nicholson and Gertrude Streets
Free City Circle Tram to Victoria Parade
City loop train to Parliament Station
Bus routes 250, 251 and 402 to Rathdowne Street
Making a trip to the city? Take a V/Line train

Car Park
Book a car park online and save up to 40%.
Located under Melbourne Museum, our car park is open 7 days a week from 6.00am to midnight daily. Enter via Rathdowne Street or Nicholson Street.


FOOD & DRINK

We have some of Melbourne’s best food trucks at the fair and will serve all types of tasty food and drinks. Yes, there will be coffee ;-)





ATM

An ATM is on-site, it is a good idea to bring cash along in case they are out of order or for your own convenience.






ACCESS

The Royal Exhibition Building is wheelchair and pram friendly.






BABY NEEDS

You will be able to change your little ones nappy at the Feeding area and take some time out in the relaxing feeding area.

name.html: BMW PGA CHAMPIONSHIP 2019

description.text:
FAQs



Grandstands may be available at the box office on the day, subject to availability.





When will I receive my tickets? 
Please note that all entry tickets ordered will be dispatched between a month and 2 weeks prior to the event. 



What is the Pro-AM Autographs policy?
A new autograph and selfie policy will be in place at this year’s BMW PGA Championship Celebrity Pro-Am to help with pace of play and ensure the best possible player and spectator experience. 
Players and celebrities will only stop for autographs and selfies at four designated zones:

At the rear of the practice ground before the two shotgun starts (8am and 1.15pm)
To the right of the fifth tee
To the left of the 14th tee
The walk between the 18th green and the first tee (Autograph Hill) 

No autographs or selfies will be permitted elsewhere on the golf course outside of these areas. 
Autograph items will be limited to one per person. Professional Autograph Hunters will not be allowed to approach players and celebrities. Event security will be briefed to remove those individuals that choose to ignore these measures. 



What is a Concession ticket?
Concession Tickets: These are available for customer who are aged 60 and over, registered disabled, students (with a valid student card)  and children 14 to 17.

Junior Admission:   Under 14's are admitted free of charge when accompanied by an adult on all days. 




Can I purchase tickets at the Gate?
Tickets sold at the gate are subject to availability, we suggest to buy in advance to avoid any disappointment. Please noted that a higher price will apply for on the day sales. 




When can I buy Grandstand tickets?
Grandstand tickets are available to purchase on our ticketing platform the same as admission tickets. 



Are there Blue Badge Holders' facilities?
The event is fully organized for Blue Badge Holders.
Scooters will be available for hire – please book in advance at www.eventmobility.org.uk or calling 01386 725 391
Blue Badge Holders' can reqest a free carer ticket by emailing tickets@europeantour.com



What are my transport/parking options getting to the event?
Further details on transportantion and parking options will be released closer to the event.
All BMW and MINI owners have free on-site parking.



What can/can't I bring to the event?
Prohibited Items:Detailed on the back of the ticket  
No picnics / picnic hampers allowed  
The use of mobile phones is welcomed and the European tour encourages fans to enjoy and share your experience on social media. Please ensure your phone is on silent at all times. Please ensure your flash functionality is switched off at all times. Mobile phone photography for personal use is permitted throughout the week in all areas of the course. Video capture is allowed throughout the week in non- competition areas only, such as practice facilities and mobile phone zones. Phone calls are allowed in non-competition areas only, such as practice facilities and mobile phone zones. 
Data use (texting, email, using the European Tour app, social media) is permitted at all times
At all times, please take care to avoid disturbing players and please respond to all requests from tournament staff, security, players and members of their team
Making or distributing broadcasts, commentary, news reports, data, results or statistics by any meansin any format or media including any such by mobile phone or other wireless device is not permitted.Ticket holders consent to being photographed, filmed and recorded at the Tournament (including by CCTV), and consent to use of any such film, image or recording at the discretion of the promoter and/or European Tour and their licensees and partners without compensation or notice.
No dogs (other than guide dogs) or other animals are permitted on the course.
All promotional, commercial, political, religious or offensive items of whatever nature including, butnot limited to, clothing, banners, signs, symbols and leaflets are prohibited.The ticket holder must comply with all relevant statutes, signs, safety announcements, directions ofstewards and ground regulations whilst attending the Tournament. Breach of any of these conditionsor any unacceptable behaviour likely to cause damage, nuisance or injury shall enable the venue orevent management to revoke this ticket and to eject the holder without compensation.



Where can I contact the organiser with any questions?
Please contact European Tour ticket office
By email:  tickets@europeantour.com
For hospitalty options,  please contact our dedicated hospitality team on 01344 840681 to discuss your requirements



Can I re-sell my ticket(s)?
Tickets cannot be re-sold. Any resale of the ticket/s will render them void.The ticket remains the property of the Tournament at all times.




What is the refund policy?
Ticket sales are final. No exchange or refund can be made.



Do I have to bring my printed ticket to the event?
Printed tickets must be brought to the venue. Lost, stolen or damaged tickets cannot be replaced.

description.text:
Join us for the 2019 Brooklyn Army Terminal (BAT) Block Party! 
                              Featuring live musical performances by 
                 JoJo and The Soul Rebels with special guest Talib Kweli & DJ Boston Chery! 

The BAT Block Party is FREE! and open to all ages. 
DATE: Sunday, September 8th
TIME: 12 pm – 6 pm

The Day’s Activities Will Include:

Local Food Vendors & Beer and Wine Garden (with local breweries & wineries)
Art Gallery and Local Artisan Marketplace
Guided Yoga
Fun Children’s Activities (kite-making, face-painting, and more)
Outdoor Rock Wall

Free Brooklyn Army Terminal t-shirts and baseball hats for the first 250 attendees!
Please only reserve the necessary tickets for your group.  Your ticket will be required to enter the event. You can either check-in with your mobile device or print your ticket and bring it with you to the Block Party.
...........................................

Public TransportationVIA NYC FERRY: Take the NYC Ferry’s South Brooklyn or Rockaway routes to Sunset Park.
VIA SUBWAY: N and R lines to 59th Street in Brooklyn. Exit the subway on 58th Street. Walk west on 58th Street one block toward the elevated expressway and the waterfront. Continue down 58th Street until you arrive at the waterfront.
VIA BUS: The B11 stops at 58th Street and 1st Avenue. The waterfront is just a couple minutes walk from here. The B37 Bus stops at 58th Street and 3rd Avenue. Walk west on 58th Street three blocks toward the elevated expressway and the waterfront.
............................................
The following will NOT be allowed at the Block Party:
• Outside beverages of any type• Large backpacks or bags• Smoking on campus, including e-cigarettes/vape pens• Pets• Outside music audible to others

What can I bring into the event?
Please see the list above for items not allowed. We recommend a small clear bag for personal possessions.
How can I contact the organizer with any questions?
Please visit our website for more details and contact information: bat.nyc
Do I have to bring my ticket to the event?
Yes. Please register through this Eventbrite and bring the printed ticket or proof of registration on your phone to the Block Party. bat.nyc/blockparty
Is my ticket transferrable?
We are asking that everyone register in advance to the Block Party. If your friend would like to register for you that is okay, just be sure to bring the Eventbrite confirmation form or proof of registration on your phone. Please only reserve tickets for your group. We ask that you do not hold large blocks of tickets without your guest names. 
Is it ok if the name on my ticket or registration doesn't match the person who attends?
We are asking that everyone register in advance to the Block Party. If your friend would like to register for you that is okay, just be sure to bring the Eventbrite confirmation form or proof of registration on your phone.
